23 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
24 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
25 Article – Business Regulation
26 2–111.
27 THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
28 (1) ESTABLISH A PROCESS THROUGH WHICH A PERSON MAY
29 RECOMMEND A VOCATIONAL, WORKFORCE, TRAINING, OR JOB PLACEMENT
30 PROGRAM FOR INCLUSION IN THE DATABASE DEVELOPED AND MAINTAINED UNDER
31 § 15–160 OF THE HEALTH – GENERAL ARTICLE; AND
32 (2) IF APPROPRIATE, FORWARD A RECOMMENDATION MADE UNDER
33 ITEM (1) OF THIS SECTION TO THE MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH FOR
34 INCLUSION IN THE DATABASE.
35 Article – Health – General

SENATE BILL 772 3
1 15–160.
2 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “DATABASE” MEANS THE EMPLOYMENT TRAINING
3 AND OPPORTUNITY DATABASE DEVELOPED AND MAINTAINED UNDER SUBSECTION
4 (B) OF THIS SECTION.
5 (B) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DEVELOP AND MAINTAIN AN
6 EMPLOYMENT TRAINING AND OPPORTUNITY DATABASE.
7 (2) THE PURPOSE OF THE DATABASE IS TO PROVIDE INDIVIDUALS IN
8 THE STATE WITH ASSISTANCE IN FINDING EMPLOYMENT TRAINING AND OTHER
9 OPPORTUNITIES THAT MAY ENABLE THE INDIVIDUALS TO BECOME ELIGIBLE AND
10 MAINTAIN ELIGIBILITY FOR:
11 (I) THE PROGRAM; AND
12 (II) THE SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION ASSISTANCE PROGRAM.
13 (3) IN DEVELOPING AND MAINTAINING THE DATABASE, THE
14 DEPARTMENT SHALL COORDINATE WITH THE FOLLOWING ENTITIES:
15 (I) THE MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF LABOR;
16 (II) THE DEPARTMENT OF HUMAN SERVICES;
17 (III) THE DEPARTMENT OF SERVICE AND CIVIC INNOVATION;
18 (IV) THE MARYLAND CHAMBER OF COMMERCE;
19 (V) LABOR UNIONS;
20 (VI) TRADE ASSOCIATIONS;
21 (VII) EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS;
22 (VIII) LOCAL WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT BOARDS; AND
23 (IX) ANY OTHER ENTITY THAT THE DEPARTMENT DETERMINES
24 APPROPRIATE.
25 (C) THE DATABASE SHALL INCLUDE:

4 SENATE BILL 772
1 (1) VOCATIONAL, WORKFORCE TRAINING, AND JOB PLACEMENT
2 PROGRAMS AVAILABLE IN THE STATE;
3 (2) INFORMATION REGARDING HOW TO APPLY FOR A VOCATIONAL,
4 WORKFORCE TRAINING, OR JOB PLACEMENT PROGRAM INCLUDED IN THE
5 DATABASE UNDER ITEM (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION; AND
6 (3) A MECHANISM THAT ALLOWS AN INDIVIDUAL TO DIRECTLY
7 CONTACT THE VOCATIONAL, WORKFORCE TRAINING, OR JOB PLACEMENT PROGRAM
8 IN WHICH THE INDIVIDUAL IS INTERESTED.
9 (D) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
10 (1) MAKE THE DATABASE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC ON A
11 DEDICATED PAGE ON THE DEPARTMENT’S WEBSITE;
12 (2) ASSIST INDIVIDUALS IN ENROLLING IN VOCATIONAL,
13 WORKFORCE TRAINING, AND JOB PLACEMENT PROGRAMS LISTED IN THE
14 DATABASE; AND
15 (3) UPDATE THE DATABASE AT LEAST EVERY 30 DAYS.
16 Article – Human Services
17 5–101.
18 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
19 (g) “Secretary” means the Secretary of Human Services.
20 5–304.
21 (b) (1) The Secretary of Budget and Management, with the assistance of the
22 Secretary, shall develop and implement a plan for hiring current and former recipients,
23 children of current or former recipients, foster youth, and obligors by the principal
24 departments within the Executive Branch of State government.
25 (c) (1) Working with appropriate local government officials, the Secretary and
26 each local director shall develop and implement a local government hiring plan under which
27 local governments may hire current and former recipients, children of current or former
28 recipients, foster youth, and obligors.
29 (D) THE SECRETARY SHALL:

